# 💬 ChatterUp

A real-time, minimal, and responsive chat application built using **React**, **Vite**, **Tailwind CSS**, **Express**, **Socket.IO**, and **MongoDB**.

---

## 🚀 Live Demo

Frontend: [https://chatterup.vercel.app](https://chatterup.vercel.app)  
Backend API: [https://chatappbackend-4f4o.onrender.com](https://chatappbackend-4f4o.onrender.com)

---

## 📦 Features

- 🧑‍💻 Real-time chat with WebSockets (Socket.IO)
- 🧑‍🤝‍🧑 Join/leave notifications
- ✍️ Typing indicators
- 💡 Theme toggle (light/dark)
- 🎭 Avatar generation using DiceBear
- 🔌 MongoDB persistence (chat history)
- ⚡ Lightweight UI using React + Tailwind CSS
- 💬 Responsive design for mobile and desktop

---

## 📂 Project Structure

chatterUp/
├── backend/
│ ├── config/
│ │ └── db.js
│ ├── controllers/
│ │ └── socketController.js
│ ├── server.js
│ └── .env
├── frontend/
│ ├── src/
│ │ ├── components/
│ │ ├── context/
│ │ ├── utils/
│ │ └── main.jsx
│ ├── public/
│ └── vite.config.js


---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

**Frontend**: React + Vite + Tailwind CSS  
**Backend**: Express + Socket.IO + MongoDB  
**Hosting**: Vercel (frontend), Render (backend)

---

## 🧑‍💻 Local Development

### ⚙️ Backend Setup

1. Navigate to the backend folder:
   ```bash
   cd backend
Install dependencies:


npm install
Create a .env file:


MONGO_URI=your_mongodb_connection_string
PORT=5000
Run server:


node server.js
🖥️ Frontend Setup
Open a new terminal, navigate to frontend:


cd frontend
Install dependencies:


npm install
Run development server:


npm run dev
App will open at http://localhost:5173

🌐 Hosting Info
Frontend deployed to Vercel (frontend/ as root directory)

Backend deployed to Render (web service)

Uses socket.connect() only on chat join, not on page load

CORS configured to allow both local and hosted frontend


